race.comment: OPENING ADDRESS (3) looks well placed with a run under the belt. His return at Seymour with 62kg was a good effort to finish fourth with improvement to come. He's always had ability and did run a good seventh in the G1 Australian Guineas second up over this trip last time in. Rates highly now out to a mile. SHINY NEW DEEL (6) had been threatening to put down a big win and did just that last start at Sandown Hillside, scoring by 2.75 lengths. Fresh for the slight drop back in trip and does draw nicely. EVERYTHING COUNTS (7) has been going well this time in, not far away in fourth at his past two since a fresh win. Can roll forward and looks to have found a suitable race. POLITELY DUN (4) is first up. This is short of his best but his 3yo form over a trip reads well and he has to be respected. ENTRUSTING (10) has been okay in two runs back and should be fitter now.
